# Set the seed.
    rng = np.random.default_rng(seed)

    # Generate the distribution.
    num_samples = 1000
    samples = rng.normal(mu, sigma, num_samples)

    # Set the color bar and its ticks.
    sns.set_theme(style="darkgrid")

    # Plot the distribution.
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(samples, bins="auto")
    ax.set_xlim((-3.2, 3.2))
    ax.set_xticks([mu - (1.96*sigma), mu, mu + (1.96*sigma)])
    ax.set_xticklabels(["1.96σ", "μ", "1.96σ"])
    ax.set_title(f"μ = {mu:.2f}, σ = {sigma:.2f}")

    return ax
